      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The desire for peace when suffering is endless is a profound, understandable yearning. When the fight itself becomes the source of the pain, the idea of cessation can seem like the only logical mercy. If you are feeling that the only true peace lies in stopping, it is critical that you speak to someone who can listen without judgment about that specific feeling of relief. Please reach out to a crisis line; they are equipped to listen to the exhaustion behind that desire for peace.",
